patch.comment: Improve the Markdown target to show hyperlinked "extends" and "implements" types for class and interface APIs

minor.comment: For markdown output, parameter types and return types are now hyperlinked to the corresponding API item

patch.comment: Properly encode xrefs that contain '#' characters.

Replace dependencies whose NPM scope was renamed from `@microsoft` to `@rushstack`
Upgrade Node typings to Node 10

minor.comment: Add a new command-line option --new-docfx-namespaces to improve how namespaces are represented when generating YAML for DocFX
Make newline type for generated files configurable

patch.comment: Update repository URL
Disambiguate output files for items with colliding names
Updating OfficeYamlDocumenter to account for new deeply linked types
Update documentation
Add support for emitting deeply linked types in YamlDocumenter

minor.comment: For the markdown target, generate an "index.md" file with an inventory of documented packages

patch.comment: (Experimental) Expand the API for API Documenter plugins
(Experimental) Introduce an API for writing API Documenter plugins
Update TSDoc dependency to 0.12.14
Improve algorithm for UID generation to prevent certain naming collisions (e.g. between static/instance members with the same name)
Fix an issue where generated filenames sometimes mcontained invalid characters
Avoid reporting a fatal error when an unknown block tag is encountered
Add support for emitting type parameters in the YamlDocumenter
Fix an issue where TSDoc index selectors (ApiParameterListMixin.overloadIndex) started from 0, whereas TSDoc requires a nonzero number

minor.comment: Improved the experimental api-documenter generate command.

patch.comment: Improve the markdown generator to document class constructors

Fix newline rendering when code blocks are used in tables
Adding an extra newline to the OfficeYamlDocumenter Examples header insertion

patch.comment: Add 'do not edit' header to generated documentation files
Add limited support for resolving @inheritDoc references to external packages by postprocessing them in api-documenter
Fix an issue with type unions rendering in markdown tables (addresses #1065)
Refactor code to move the IndentedWriter API from api-extractor-model to api-documenter
Upgrade TSDoc
Update api-documenter to use the new NPM package @microsoft/api-extractor-model; eliminate dependencies on @microsoft/api-extractor or the TypeScript compiler
Fix issue where docs were not generated for function parameters and return types (GitHub #1055)
Upgrade to TSDoc 0.12.5
[api-documenter] Enable Office snippets to match multiple versions
MarkdownEmitter: break for inline tags

Work around an issue where GitHub Pages cannot render `

` inside a pipes-and-dashes table (even though GHFM supports this)
Support more API types for the markdown generator: namespace, function, type alias, variable
Update to work with refactored ApiModel classes
Update web site URLs

Updated to use the new InternalError class for reporting software defects

Update URLs in OfficeYamlDocumenter
Update "repository" field in package.json
Republish all packages in web-build-tools to resolve GitHub issue #782
render markdown for namespace; fix api ref check for namespace
Allow markdown to continue generating when api reference check failed
Updating OfficeYamlDocumenter to append snippets to non-empty sections

patch.comment: Changing Office's APIExtractor add-on to unescape characters in code blocks

minor.comment: The YAML target now automatically hyperlinks type references, but only if the type name is simple and not ambiguous

minor.comment: Add support for rendering the new IMarkupHtmlTag

Update API Set URL resolution in OfficeYamlDocumenter
